text: Camille Iquliq (1963–2005) was an Inuit artist. She began carving in 1984. Her work is included in the collections of the Government of Nunavut Fine Art Collection and the Musee national des beaux-arts du Quebec. She died in 2005 as a result of cancer. ==References== Category: 1963 births Category:2005 deaths Category:20th-century Canadian women artists Category:Inuit artists Category:21st-century Canadian women artists
